minimal documentation for mu
----------------------------

1. installing
   - run "sudo ant install"
   - you now have /usr/local/bin/mu

2. using
   - go to an empty directory
   - make a file that looks like this:
       org:  myorg.com
       proj: NeatProj
       ver:  1.0
       lang: Java
       type:
           - app
       uses:
           - commons-*.jar
       main: com.myorg.neat.Main
   - put your sources in src/main/java
   - put your resources in src/resources
   - put your dependent jars in ~/.mu/lib
   - run "mu app.run"

3. the door, the future
   - mu can do many other things, but they are not documented. todo.
